Today focused heavily on reinforcing foundational grammar and reviewing weak areas identified during earlier Pimsleur lessons. Duolingo and Memrise practice introduced additional vocabulary related to locations, household objects, and descriptive language, while also reinforcing sentence recognition and reading comprehension.

Pimsleur review continued with Unit 1 Lessons 20 and 21. Extra emphasis was placed on Lesson 21 due to repeated confusion with:
- demonstratives (this/that/these/those)
- masculine vs feminine agreement
- singular vs plural agreement
- “leaving” structures involving different people

Key grammar concepts reviewed included:
- este / esta / estos / estas
- me voy / te vas / se va / nos vamos / se van

Significant improvement was shown by the end of practice rounds in correctly identifying and using demonstratives with proper gender and plurality.

Core Pimsleur phrases reviewed included:
- “Me voy ahora”
- “Nos vamos juntos”
- “Se va solo”
- “¿Te vas mañana?”
- “¿Quién es esa mujer?”
- “No quiero hablar ahora”
- “¿Cuántas personas hay aquí?”

The weekly travel-focused conversational phrases were also reviewed again as preparation for the upcoming Puerto Rico trip. Practice focused on:
- airport navigation
- reservations
- hotel check-in
- restaurant interactions
- ordering food naturally

Key travel phrases practiced:
- “¿Dónde está la puerta de embarque?”
